cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel Bayesian meta-learning method that combines scalable gradient-based meta-learning with nonparametric variational inference in a probabilistic framework. The method is evaluated on various tasks such as sinusoidal regression, image classification, active learning, and reinforcement learning. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper focuses on meta-learning and Bayesian inference. The other likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper also evaluates the proposed method on image classification tasks. The paper also discusses reinforcement learning, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
